i'll explain now ....

most things that are done with edhrec i tend to want them to be well thought out and guaranteed to succeed before i do it and be done with a purpose. On that point, I think we can do that with a discord if we want to. I just want to have it be more planned out with my concerns particularly addressed and have the proper investment (time and $ involved). In that, it needs to be a high enough priority for me to be invested in, and honestly with the other cool stuff i have planned i can't say i place it very high, and i'll explain that too in a second.

For my concerns for the discord, it's mostly about involvement of the current EDHREC community. I can say for certain I personally won't be very active which might be a bummer for some people looking to ask about edhrec features, or suggest features or whatever. Also, I'd want a bit more of a commitment from the rest of us that we would all be active while articles get put up, etc.. and I don't think we have that. In a bit of a go big or go home sense, if this is something I'd want to do "right" I'd want to blow all the other EDH discords out of the water, which is a competitive space right now. I'd want to have the best people around, I'd might even want some integration with articles and even the site pages, and probably some other cool things we can think of.

The downside of being as big as EDHREC is we can't fiddle around with an idea and kinda waltz into it. People expect certain things and if it's not good enough we only get one chance and it messes with the rest of the branding.

In summary, to convince me to get on board with a discord, we need to figure out:
 - how to properly moderate the discord so it's fine with all audiences. Most discords I've been in are cesspools and for us we need it to not be that
 - most people here are involved
 - integrations with core EDHREC are thought out and implemented
 - how this is going to directly impact EDHREC's traffic, brand, whatever
 - clearly outline the risks
